# k3d

> Wrapper CLI to easily create k3s clusters inside Docker
> More information: https://k3d.io

- Create a cluster:

`k3d cluster create {any something}`

- Delete a cluster:

`k3d cluster delete {any something}`

- Create a new containerized k3s node:

`k3d node create {any something}`

- Import an image from Docker into a k3d cluster:

`k3d image import {any something} --cluster {any something}`

- Create a new registry:

`k3d registry create {any something}`
